limitations

*TABLES*

// <x>id has prefix, e.g., oid:deadface for oid

// an account has a separate db to store its orders,
// trades, postions, portfolios and cash, etc.

order: oid -> ctpIDS, orderstatus, tradevolume, _ptfid, _strat

order2trade: oid -> list of tid

trade: tradeid -> ctptradeid, price, volume, inst, direction, time, exchange, _oid

(portfolio here means a realization of portfolio definition)
portfolio order: ptfid -> _oids, by inst
portfolio progress: ptfid -> inst trade amount / avgprice

(portfolio is a subset of orders, trades and postions, or a sub-account)

position: inst+direction: volume, avgprice, margin, pnl(a property)
(position is an aggreation of trades)
